Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on stone block showing figures of three giraffes and two unidentified figures, pecked and infilled with pecking, all upright and facing right. Largest giraffe is central, naturalistic and standing. Two further run one occluding the other as if abreast, above the central giraffe, towards unidentified animal (antelope?) with head cut off by shadow at top right of image. At lower right unidentified animal also cut off at shoulder at edge of image. 10cm photo scale fitted at base of image. New Kalabsha, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
